King Zwelonke Sigcawu was quoted saying that the country was not ready for a female president. JOHANNESBURG - AmaXhosa King Zwelonke Sigcawu says that he has been misunderstood by the media over his comments about women leading the country.The king was quoted last week saying that the country was not ready for a female president because men had not been able turn things around in the country.He was speaking at a gathering at his Nqadu Great Place in the Eastern Cape during a visit by former African Union chairperson Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma.He also says he was not referring to Dlamini-Zuma when he made the comments and that the media linked it to her because she was present.The Commission for Gender Equity has since condemned his comments saying that is in violation of the constitution.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)